Note: Tkinter is included by default in Python.

Run the application:

bash
Copy code
python ui/app.py
Usage
Create a new chat session using the "New" button.

Select a session to send and receive messages.

Messages from bots simulate auto-replies.

Use the search bar to filter sessions or search messages in a session.

Dependencies
Python 3.8+

Tkinter (GUI library, included in standard Python)

Standard libraries: datetime, threading, time

Folder Structure
graphql
Copy code
Simple_Chat_Messaging_Simulator/
├── engine/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── builder.py           # ChatSessionBuilder to create chat sessions
│   ├── chat_engine.py       # ChatEngine singleton managing sessions & observers
│   ├── session.py           # ChatSession class definition
├── messages/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── base_message.py      # Base Message class
│   ├── text_message.py      # Text message type
│   ├── system_message.py    # System messages
│   ├── decorators.py        # Message decorators (e.g., TimestampDecorator)
│   ├── factory.py           # Factory to create message types
├── patterns/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── observer.py          # Observer interface
│   ├── singleton.py         # Singleton base class for ChatEngine
├── ui/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── gui.py               # Main GUI class (Tkinter)
│   ├── app.py               # Entry point to launch the application
├── README.md                # Project description and instructions
└── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies (optional)
Design Pattern Usage
Observer Pattern
Problem Solved: Decouples the Chat Engine and GUI for real-time updates.

Implementation: ChatEngine acts as the subject; ChatGUI subscribes as the observer.

Classes:

scss
Copy code
ChatEngine (Subject)
 └─ subscribe(observer)
 └─ notify(event, payload)

ChatGUI (Observer)
 └─ update(event, payload)
Factory Pattern
Problem Solved: Dynamically creates message objects without hardcoding.

Implementation: MessageFactory.create(type, sender, text) generates text, system, or bot messages.

Classes:

pgsql
Copy code
MessageFactory
 └─ create(type, sender, text) → returns Message / SystemMessage / BotMessage
Decorator Pattern
Problem Solved: Adds timestamps or formatting to messages at runtime.

Implementation: TimestampDecorator wraps a message and renders it with a timestamp.

Classes:

scss
Copy code
TimestampDecorator
 └─ __init__(message)
 └─ render() → returns formatted string
Singleton Pattern
Problem Solved: Ensures only one Chat Engine instance exists.

Implementation: ChatEngine inherits from a singleton base class.

Known Issues
Auto-reply bot has a fixed response delay.

Search currently works for text messages only.

Notification badges update slower when many sessions exist.

Messages and sessions are not persisted after closing the application.
Future Enhancements

Implement message persistence (save chats to files or database).

Add multimedia message support (images, emojis).

Customizable bot responses and typing speed.

Improve search functionality with message filtering.
